<h1>Terms of Service</h1>
<p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> 1 June 2025</p>

<p class="muted">
  These Terms of Service apply to paraplanning, operational support and advisory services provided by
  Beyond Paraplanning & Intelligent Adviser Solutions (“Beyond”, “we”, “us”). By instructing Beyond, the Client
  agrees to be bound by these terms.
</p>

<div class="callout">
  <strong>Important:</strong> Beyond provides professional support and advisory services. We do not provide regulated financial advice
  to end clients and we do not assume responsibility for the suitability of recommendations made by the Client.
</div>

<h2>1. Services Provided</h2>
<p>Beyond provides support services to independent financial advisers and firms. Services may include:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Paraplanning and report writing (e.g. suitability reports, annual review reports)</li>
  <li>Research and technical support (e.g. comparisons, provider information, product / platform analysis)</li>
  <li>Operational projects (e.g. process design, MI, workflow improvement, file / template systems)</li>
  <li>Strategic and structural support (e.g. capacity, segmentation, service standards, operating rhythm)</li>
  <li>Custom tools and templates (e.g. Word / Excel assets, flowcharts, checklists)</li>
</ul>

<h2>2. Instruction, Delivery and Turnaround</h2>
<p>
  Instructions should be provided in writing (email, Teams or agreed channel) with sufficient detail and relevant supporting information.
  Turnaround times will be agreed on a case-by-case basis and may depend on complexity and the completeness of information provided.
</p>
<p>
  The Client is responsible for reviewing all deliverables and confirming accuracy before use. Any regulated communications to end clients
  remain the responsibility of the Client.
</p>

<h2>3. Fees and Payment Terms</h2>
<p><strong>Hourly Services:</strong> £60 per hour unless otherwise agreed in writing.</p>
<p><strong>Report Writing:</strong> Fixed pricing where quoted. Multi-area, complex or bespoke cases may be quoted separately.</p>
<p><strong>Projects:</strong> Quoted in writing prior to commencement, typically with a 50% deposit payable upfront and the balance payable prior to delivery, unless otherwise agreed.</p>

<p><strong>Invoices:</strong> Payable within 7 calendar days of issue unless otherwise agreed in writing.</p>
<p><strong>Late Payment:</strong> Invoices unpaid after 14 days may incur a 2% monthly fee. If payment remains outstanding, Beyond reserves the right to pause work until the account is brought up to date.</p>

<h2>4. Cancellations and Changes</h2>
<p>
  Where work is instructed and subsequently cancelled, the Client remains responsible for fees relating to work completed up to the point of cancellation.
  For projects, deposits are non-refundable once work has commenced.
</p>
<p>
  If scope changes materially following instruction, Beyond may re-quote or revise time and cost estimates before continuing.
</p>

<h2>5. Confidentiality and Data Protection</h2>
<p>
  Beyond will treat all non-public information as confidential and will not disclose it without written consent, unless required by law.
  We act as a data processor where applicable and comply with relevant data protection obligations.
  Please refer to our <a href="privacy-notice.html">Privacy Notice</a> for details.
</p>
<p>
  The Client warrants that they have the lawful basis to share any client data required for the provision of services.
</p>

<h2>6. Client Responsibilities</h2>
<p>The Client is responsible for:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Providing accurate, complete and timely information</li>
  <li>Responding to queries, approvals and requests promptly</li>
  <li>Reviewing deliverables for accuracy and appropriateness</li>
  <li>Ensuring all regulated advice, suitability and client communications are approved and issued by the Client</li>
</ul>

<h2>7. Intellectual Property</h2>
<p>
  Unless otherwise agreed in writing, all frameworks, templates, tools and materials developed by Beyond remain the intellectual property of Beyond.
  The Client is granted a licence to use deliverables internally for their business. Sharing, resale or distribution to third parties is not permitted
  without written permission.
</p>

<h2>8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
<p>
  Beyond’s liability for any claim shall be limited to the value of the specific service giving rise to the claim.
  Beyond shall not be liable for indirect, consequential or commercial losses, including loss of profit, business or goodwill.
</p>
<p>
  Beyond does not accept responsibility for outcomes arising from the Client’s advice, recommendations, investment decisions or client communications,
  including where the Client approves or amends deliverables prior to issue.
</p>

<h2>9. Termination</h2>
<p>
  Either party may terminate ongoing arrangements with 30 days’ written notice unless otherwise agreed.
  Fees remain payable for all work completed up to the termination date.
</p>
<p>
  Beyond reserves the right to terminate immediately where payments are overdue, terms are breached, or where continued work becomes unfeasible.
</p>

<h2>10. Disputes and Governing Law</h2>
<p>
  If a dispute arises, both parties agree to attempt resolution in good faith through discussion. If unresolved, the parties will consider mediation
  before court proceedings.
</p>
<p>This agreement is governed by the laws of England and Wales.</p>

